mic, and historical contexts, the volume explores the intersection of the nation's English education with variables such as power, economy, policy, ideology, and information technology over the past three decades. The multidisciplinary insights of the book will be of value to scholars of global English, education policies and reforms and language policy as well as those who are specifically concerned with education in Iran.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEnglish languagexForeign countries. 0aEnglish languagexSpoken EnglishzIran. 0aEnglish languagexStudy and teachingzIran. 0aEnglish languagezForeign countries. 0aEnglish languagezIran. 0aLanguage policyzIran. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aEnglish education in Iran.  aIran.  afieldwork data.  alanguage and ideology.  alanguage policy.  anational identity.  apower.1 aBorjian, Maryam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Ofelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066313608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311060671340uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/9781847699107zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847699107zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847699107/original  a978-3-11-060671-3 MultiLingual Matters eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066313-6 MultiLingual Matters Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c20